statements.notes:
Raw organic chia seeds
Chia seeds are an ancient food staple, dating back to the time of the Aztecs, Incans and Mayans. They are a good source of dietary fiber, with 16% of your daily-recommended intake in just one serving! Fiber-full foods like chia seeds help to support healthy digestion and also help you feel fuller for longer after eating. The chia seeds' amazing nutritional profile also includes omega fatty acids, essential minerals, and protein.
Raw
Suggested use: Sprinkle one tablespoon (1 scoop) into oatmeal, granola, cereal or yogurt. Chia seeds also work as a flour substitute, and can be ground and used to make baked goods.
Visit www.bareorganics.com for great recipes and ideas.
